Rating: 4
I have been making this every year (up to 5 times a year...I know, I know) for the past 9 years. It is one of my best and favorite recipes. It looks gorgeous--I've mastered the knack of making the marbling look like a big flower on top--and it tastes like the best, creamiest pumpkin pie you've ever had. Simply divine. I started out making it precisely as written. Currently the alterations I make are 1) graham cracker crust of 1.5 c crumbs, 5.5 T melted butter, 1/3 c brown sugar; 2) double the spices, 3) bake at 350 (I firmly believe 550 was a typo) for 20 min, then 200 for 1 hr 20 min, then turn off oven and leave in unopened oven for 20 min. I make it in a springform pan, so it's important to loosen the sides with a wet knife as soon as it comes out of the oven then let is slowly cool on the counter to room temp before putting it in the fridge--never cracks that way. I have probably been asked for this recipe almost 2 dozen times. Enjoy.

