Rating: 4
Excellent cheesecake. Here are my recommendations after having read all the other reviews: 1) I use 350 for 20 minutes then 200 for 1:20 then leave it to cool in the oven for another 20. You can fast cook it at 350 for one hour, but I find slow cooking to give much better results, unless you're in a rush for some reason. 2) I suspect 550 was to brown the top as to get the effect shown in the picture, but I do not think it is necessary and you're more liable to burn the cheesecake this way. I've never seen any cheesecake (let alone normal) recipe call for scorching it at 550. 3) I baked this twice, once using a waterbath at 325, there was no appreciable difference. Cheescakes aren't particularly picky, there are a hundred variations from other reviewers that all probably should work equally well. 4) Unlike one reviewer, I did not find the cheesecake too sweet with the stated sugar. 5) Add some crushed pecans to the crust. 6) The crust should not crack at all. Just be sure to follow the directions to loosen the cake so that it can bend inward slightly as it cools, this will prevent it from cracking. Do not bake the crust beforehand.

