Rating: 4
I want to let everyone know that this is an award-winning recipe! I made it for the first time as a contest entry - the only rule of the contest was that it must contain pumpkin. My only experience with pumpkin has been with the traditional pie, and pumpkin bread. At the suggestion of my cousin, I logged onto Epicurious.com to find something new and exciting to enter in the contest. I was totally up in the air as to what I would choose. The cheesecake sounded great, so that was my choice. The cheesecake is time consuming, and a somewhat delicate operation. I say this, because as I was slipping the cake into the refrigerator at the end of the entire process, the cake began to slip from the plate. I had to grab the cake on top with my whole hand to stop it from slipping to the floor. This frantic grab left a huge and deep handprint in the top of the cake. I was just sick about it and almost didn't enter it in the contest. After consulting with friends, decided to do my best to camouflage the sunken in area: Just before judging was to begin, I sprayed "a whole lot" of Reddi-Whip over the hand, and then went around the edges of the cake with the same stuff. Sprinkled chopped pecans and orange and brown sprinkles around the edges also. (I know this sounds tacky but it looked quite nice - contest was just before Halloween too, which worked out well for me. Ha!) Imagine my shock when I was told that I had won first place and comments were made about the delightful blending of flavors and the smooth and rich texture. Go for it! This is a great recipe. (I also made it this past Thanksgiving and it made a big hit with the family.) Bon Appetit! Betty

