Rating: 4
This cheesecake sounded like a great alternative to pumpkin pie for Thanksgiving so I tried it but instead of the scary 550 temp. I baked it the same way I have baked my old standby NY style cheesecake for the past 32 years - in a waterbath (outside of 9" springform pan covered in heavyduty foil) in a preheated 325 degree oven for 1 hr. 10 min., then TURN OVEN OFF and let cake sit in oven for 2 hr., then remove and let cool completely on counter, then refrigerate for at least several hrs. or preferably, overnight. Not burned, no cracks, Perfection! Everyone raved! (gingersnap crust - abt. 32 gingersnaps, 1/4 c. sugar, 1/4 c. melted butter).

